Heat vegetable oil in a skillet over medium heat. Cook and stir egg substitute in hot oil until set, about 5 minutes. Transfer scrambled egg substitute to a plate and refrigerate until chilled. Stir chilled egg substitute, chopped egg whites, mashed potato, mayonnaise, green onions, celery, mustard, chili powder, garlic powder, balsamic vinegar, salt, and black pepper in a bowl until combined.